metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, in my head is more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension and Chord Progression Novelty.
key_conclusion: in my head has sections analyzed in the following keys: G Major,  and E Minor.  Click on the linked cheat sheets for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: My most favorite song from Ari's "thank u, next" album. It's like the Bad Decisions" but from said album lol. Although due to the absence of the "I" chord (G, Gmaj7 or G with some inversion), also the lack of the "vi" chord (Em) and the sole presence of the Câ€“Bm chords I refused to believe that the key of this song was G Ionian, and that instead it was C Lydian, B Phrygian, or even E Aeolian; this was what caught my attention the most about this song and makes it so rare and special. However, I started to analyze the acapella notes and most of them are red (G), so now I agree with @Stational, thanks for my knowledge :) P.S. This section can also work as the instrumental.
